âœ… 1. Built-in CI/CD: GitHub Actions
GitHub Actions allows you to automate workflows like building, testing, and deploying applications.

ğŸ”§ Example: CI pipeline for a Node.js app
yaml

# .github/workflows/nodejs.yml
name: Node.js CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]
  pull_request:
    branches: [ main ]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
    - uses: actions/checkout@v3
    - name: Set up Node.js
      uses: actions/setup-node@v3
      with:
        node-version: 18
    - run: npm install
    - run: npm test
âœ… Triggers on every push/pull request to main, installs dependencies, and runs tests.

  

âœ… 2. Pull Requests: Review and Merge Changes
Pull Requests (PRs) are used to:

Propose code changes

Get peer reviews

Run automated tests before merging

ğŸ”§ Example: Workflow
Dev creates a feature branch: git checkout -b feature/login-api

Pushes code: git push origin feature/login-api

Creates PR on GitHub: Reviewers get notified

GitHub Actions run tests automatically

After approval, it's merged into main

ğŸ” Ensures clean code, peer review, and no broken features in main.

  

âœ… 3. Webhooks: Trigger Events Like Jenkins/Slack
Webhooks send HTTP POST payloads to a URL when something happens in the repo.

ğŸ”§ Example: Jenkins CI Trigger from GitHub
In GitHub:

Go to your repo â†’ Settings â†’ Webhooks â†’ Add Webhook

URL: http://<your-jenkins-url>/github-webhook/

Content type: application/json

Trigger: Push events

In Jenkins:

Create a Jenkins pipeline job

Enable â€œGitHub hook trigger for GITScm pollingâ€

âœ… Now, whenever you push to GitHub, Jenkins gets triggered automatically.

ğŸ”§ Example: Slack Notification Webhook
In Slack: Create an Incoming Webhook URL

In GitHub Actions:

yaml
Copy
Edit
- name: Slack Notify
  uses: slackapi/slack-github-action@v1.23.0
  with:
    payload: |
      {
        "text": "âœ… CI Passed for ${{ github.repository }} on commit ${{ github.sha }}"
      }
  env:
    SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL: ${{ secrets.SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL }}


âœ… 4. Integration with Other Tools
ğŸ”§ Jira Integration
Link GitHub commits/issues to Jira tickets

Example commit message:
git commit -m "JIRA-123: Fixed login redirect bug"

If Jira + GitHub are connected (via GitHub Marketplace or Jira Cloud), this will link your PR/commit directly to the Jira ticket.

ğŸ”§ Jenkins Integration
Use GitHub repo as source in Jenkins job

Add Jenkins GitHub plugin

Enable GitHub webhook triggers as above

ğŸ”§ VS Code Integration
Install GitHub extension in VS Code

You can:

Clone/push/pull from GitHub

Create & review pull requests inside the editor

Use GitHub Copilot for code suggestions

# ğŸ”§ Terraform Integration
Store your .tf files in GitHub

Use GitHub Actions to run Terraform:


- name: Terraform Init
  run: terraform init

- name: Terraform Plan
  run: terraform plan

- name: Terraform Apply
  if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'
  run: terraform apply -auto-approve
